{
  "texts": [
    "While the ideal application of DL aims to facilitate comprehensive representation learning of the underlying structures within omics data, practical challenges emerge when too few samples are available.",
    "In certain applications this can even hinder adequate representation learning and complicate the direct processing of omics data within DL frameworks.",
    "This important limitation can be mitigated using a technique called transfer learning.",
    "Unlike classical statistical models, neural networks are fitted sequentially meaning that they can be continuously updated with new data.",
    "This opens a possibility of 'pre-training' a model on some large, but weakly or partially relevant dataset and then finalizing the training on a more valuable but smaller one."
  ]
}